    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "```\r\ninsightsClient('setUserToken', 'def');\r\n\r\nsearch.EXPERIMENTAL_use(createInsightsMiddleware({ insightsClient }));\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn current implementation, if user sets userToken before creating the middleware, it will get ignored.\r\nDoes it make sense to you as long as it's documented? Or, should we allow user do that and somehow catch the token?\r\n\r\n→ For more info, the reason why this doesn't work is,\r\n`insightsClient('init', { ... })` happens when creating the middleware.\r\nIt means at the time `insightsClient('setUserToken', 'def');` is called, it's not even initialized.",
