  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@eunjae-lee Is there a use case where the Insights' `userToken` can differ from InstantSearch's? As far as I know, there's none. We could display a dev warning saying that we detected that a token was previously set, but it's ignored because of the middleware (this warning can be displayed even if the `userToken` is the same, since it's useless to set it outside of the middleware).",
