    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@francoischalifour You're talking about this, right?\r\n\r\n```js\r\ninsightsClient('setUserToken', 'def');\r\n\r\nsearch.EXPERIMENTAL_use(createInsightsMiddleware({ insightsClient }));\r\n```\r\n\r\n(To make sure we're on the same page,) user interacts with `insightsClient` to set userToken and the middleware gets updated and set the token into searchParameters. So\r\n\r\n> Is there a use case where the Insights' userToken can differ from InstantSearch's?\r\n\r\nThe answer is \"no\". And I think it makes sense to add a warning.",
